    "path": "tango/costco.md",
    "content": "# Tango Costco â€” Brain\n\n## Current Understanding\n\nMoses Romero (Asst Buyer, D13 Dry Grocery) gave good feedback on samples. He wants to discuss roadshows. Call scheduled T-F this week. This is the most exciting lead right now â€” Costco could be transformative for volume.\n\nCurrently at $0 revenue. Target: $5,000/mo.\n\n## What We've Learned\n\n- Moses prefers **phone calls over email** â€” don't email, call\n- He's an Assistant Buyer in D13 (Dry Grocery) â€” this is the right department for hot sauce\n- He responded positively to samples â€” a win given how hard it is to get Costco attention\n- Roadshows are the typical entry point for new brands at Costco â€” prove sell-through before shelf placement\n- Costco margins are tight but volume makes up for it\n\n## Key Contact\n\n- **Moses Romero** â€” Asst Buyer, D13 Dry Grocery, Costco\n- Status: âœ… GOOD FEEDBACK â€” wants roadshows\n- Prefers: Phone calls (not email)\n- Next step: Call T-F this week\n- Contact info: (check distribution/costco/ folder for details)\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- What's the roadshow timeline? When can we start?\n- What pricing works for Costco's margin requirements?\n- How many units per roadshow? What's the production commitment?\n- Which region first? (SoPac makes sense given UNFI success there)\n- Multi-pack or single bottle for Costco format?\n- What does the roadshow staffing look like? Dan has to be there?\n- What's the demo/sampling logistics?\n\n## Strategy\n\n1. **Close the call with Moses** â€” confirm roadshow interest, get timeline\n2. **Prepare roadshow pricing deck** â€” unit economics, proposed pricing, margin math\n3. **Plan production** â€” roadshows require upfront inventory commitment\n4. **Target SoPac region first** â€” already have UNFI momentum in LA\n5. **Prove sell-through** â†’ conversion to permanent shelf placement\n\n## Goal\n\n**This month:** Close roadshow deal with Moses\n**12 months:** $5,000/mo through Costco (15% of total target)\n\n## Pipeline\n\n### ðŸ“‹ To Do\n- [ ] Call Moses (T-F this week) â€” confirm roadshow details\n- [ ] Prepare roadshow pricing deck\n- [ ] Calculate unit economics for Costco pricing\n- [ ] Plan production volume for roadshow inventory\n\n### ðŸ”¨ In Progress\n(none yet)\n\n### âœ… Done\n- [x] Sent samples to Moses â€” got positive feedback\n- [x] Established phone contact preference\n\n## Files\n\n*Located at: /Projects/ðŸ”¥ tango/distribution/costco/ (if exists)*\n- Costco materials in distribution/ folder (563 files total in distribution/)\n",
    "summary": "Moses Romero (Asst Buyer, D13 Dry Grocery) gave good feedback on samples. He wants to discussâ€¦",
